    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Standpipe Bursts In Yankee Clubhouse</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Standpipe in visiting clubhouse at Shea Stadium bursts during game; New York Yankees' clubhouse is closed to news media after contest (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A standpipe in the visiting clubhouse at Shea Stadium burst during the game last night, so the Yankees' clubhouse was closed to the news media after the Yankees beat the Mets, 3-2, in Game 4 of the World Series.</p>
        <p>Major League Baseball officials said the clubhouse was flooded, and the Fire Department was on the scene to deal with the problem.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>A standpipe in the visiting clubhouse at Shea Stadium burst during the game last night, so the Yankees' clubhouse was closed to the news media after the Yankees beat the Mets, 3-2, in Game 4 of the World Series.</p>
        <p>Major League Baseball officials said the clubhouse was flooded, and the Fire Department was on the scene to deal with the problem.</p>
        <p>After the game, the Yankees were interviewed on the field, and some players were brought into the interview room. No explanation was given for how the pipe had burst.</p>
        <p>BASEBALL: SUBWAY SERIES</p>
      </block>
